<p>This theme supports two types of images:</p>

<ul>
  <li>inline images: <img src="/assets/images/batWid1.png" alt="Battery Widget" /></li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html">![Battery Widget]({{ '/assets/images/batWid1.png' | relative_url }})</code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li>centered images with caption (optional):</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/deer.jpg" alt="img" class="center-image" /><em>(Â°0Â°)</em></p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html">![img]({{ '/assets/images/deer.jpg' | relative_url }}){: .center-image }*(Â°0Â°)*</code></pre></figure>

<p>You can apply your own styles to image by creating css class with style:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="nc">.custom-image-style</span>
<span class="p">{</span>
<span class="c">/* your style */</span>
<span class="p">}</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>And then applying your style just after the image in curly brackets with colon:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html">[!image](path to image){:.custom-image-style}
 </code></pre></figure>

